# Notification Service — API tests
# Use with REST Client (VS Code / Cursor): click "Send Request" above each ###
# Start server: npm run dev  (or bun dev)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4545
@apiKey = your_api_key_here_must_be_32_chars_min
@testEmail = arjun030401@gmail.com

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Health (no auth)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Notify — single email (202 Accepted)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name notifySingle
POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": "{{testEmail}}",
  "subject": "Test — single notification",
  "html": "<h1>Hello</h1><p>Sent from api.http</p>",
  "priority": "normal"
}

### Notify — multiple recipients

POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": ["{{testEmail}}"],
  "subject": "Test — multiple recipients",
  "html": "<p>Hi team</p>",
  "priority": "high"
}

### Notify — with metadata

POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": "{{testEmail}}",
  "subject": "Test — with metadata",
  "html": "<p>Order confirmation</p>",
  "metadata": {
    "orderId": "ORD-12345",
    "source": "api.http"
  }
}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Notify — batch (up to 1000)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name notifyBatch
POST {{baseUrl}}/notify/batch
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

[
  {
    "channel": "email",
    "to": "{{testEmail}}",
    "subject": "Batch A",
    "html": "<p>Message A</p>"
  },
  {
    "channel": "email",
    "to": "{{testEmail}}",
    "subject": "Batch B",
    "html": "<p>Message B</p>"
  }
]

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Error cases (for manual verification)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 401 — missing API key

POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": "{{testEmail}}",
  "subject": "Should fail",
  "html": "<p>no key</p>"
}

### 401 — invalid API key

POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: wrong-key

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": "{{testEmail}}",
  "subject": "Should fail",
  "html": "<p>bad key</p>"
}

### 400 — validation (invalid email)

POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": "not-an-email",
  "subject": "Should fail",
  "html": "<p>bad email</p>"
}

### 400 — validation (missing subject)

POST {{baseUrl}}/notify
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "channel": "email",
  "to": "{{testEmail}}",
  "html": "<p>missing subject</p>"
}

### 404 — unknown route

GET {{baseUrl}}/does-not-exist

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Health after sending (check queue.completed / failed)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/health
